## ğŸ”§ Setup & Installation

1. Clone the repository:

    ```bash
    git clone https://github.com/Amol-2002/Android-Projects.git
    cd Android-Projects/ClassTeacherPortal
    ```

2. Open this folder in **Android Studio**  
   - Let Gradle sync and build the project  
   - Ensure you have required Android SDK & build tools installed  

3. Configure Backend API URLs (if needed)  
   - Search for API endpoint definitions (e.g. in constants or inside code)  
   - Update base URLs if your server domain/path differs  

4. Build & run the app  
   - Either run on an emulator or real Android device  
   ```bash
   flutter run  # if using Flutter; else use Android Studio â€œRunâ€ button

                                     
